headline: Snap-on Inc (SNA) Q2 2025 Earnings Call Highlights: Resilience Amidst Challenges
summary: Despite flat revenue and a dip in operating income, Snap-on Inc (SNA) shows strength in its Tools and RS&I segments, maintaining robust margins and a strong cash position.

headline: SNA Q1 Deep Dive: Tariffs and Technician Sentiment Weigh on Sales and Margins
summary: Professional tools and equipment manufacturer Snap-on (NYSE:SNA) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q2 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $1.28 billion. Its GAAP profit of $4.72 per share was 2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
